Nevermind, Used this tutorial to use reactpsn to get the game working..http://www.ps3iso.com/ps3-tutorials/184482-reactpsn-tutorial-4-30cfw-rogero.html

Don't stop seeding please. It's very slow. I haven't tried it yet but it needs react psn in order to be activated. Just copy the .rap file in a pen drive. It must be stored in a folder called "exdata", in the root of your pen drive. Then plug it into your first USB port, create a new user account called aa, install reactPSN (if you haven't already, if you already installed it just rename your reactpsn account to aa again), and then start reactpsn. Of course, all of this must be made AFTER you installed the game's pkg using multiman.
